2
1 Whereas, The following have served as legislative interns for
2 the Democratic Caucus of the Indiana House of
3 Representatives during the Second Regular Session of the 124th
4 Indiana General Assembly: Tasneem Ahmed, Elaina Bowlds,
5 Joshua Brown, Chaz Collins, Tyleah Cunningham, Frank Diaz
6 Morales, Kalina Dickinson, Avery Goldthorpe, Nathan Hogg,
7 Molly Holthe, Kyra Horton, Sam Hunt, Carson Johnson, Chelsi
8 McMahan, Melisa Mendez, and Fayrouz Mourad;
9 Whereas, The work of legislative interns is vital to the
10 success of each session of the Indiana House of
11 Representatives;
12 Whereas, The legislative interns serving in 2026 are among
13 the best and brightest future leaders of Indiana;
14 Whereas, Many former legislative interns have gone on to
15 achieve significant success in their personal, academic,
16 political, and professional lives; and
17 Whereas, The 2026 class of legislative interns consists of
18 young leaders who are poised to make positive contributions to
19 their communities and to the State of Indiana in the years
20 ahead: Therefore,
21 Be it resolved by the House of Representatives of the
22 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
23 SECTION 1. That the Indiana House of Representatives
24 recognizes the important contributions of the individuals who
25 are serving as legislative interns with the Indiana House of
26 Representatives during the Second Regular Session of the 124th
27 Indiana General Assembly.
28 SECTION 2. That the Principal Clerk of the House of
29 Representatives shall transmit copies of this resolution to State
30 Representative Greg Steuerwald for distribution.
